#. type: Title =
#: _versions/3.34/guides/logging.adoc
msgid "Configure the log level, category, and format"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/logging.adoc
msgid "JBoss Logging, integrated into {project-name}, provides a unified configuration for all <<logging-apis,supported logging APIs>> through a single configuration file that sets up all available extensions."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/logging.adoc
msgid "To adjust runtime logging, modify the `application.properties` file."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: _versions/3.34/guides/logging.adoc
msgid "An example of how you can set the default log level to `INFO` logging and include Hibernate `DEBUG` logs:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/logging.adoc
msgid "Assuming the link:https://quarkus.io/guides/config-yaml[Quarkus YAML extension] is included, the equivalent YAML configuration is:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/logging.adoc
msgid "When you set the log level to below `DEBUG`, for example `TRACE`, you must also adjust the minimum log level."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/logging.adoc
msgid "Set the minimum log level globally with the `quarkus.log.min-level` configuration property, or set it per category:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/logging.adoc
msgid ""
"The minimum log level is a build-time configuration option that sets the floor level for which Quarkus generates supporting code.\n"
"This enables further build-time optimizations, such as dead code elimination when building a native image."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: _versions/3.34/guides/logging.adoc
msgid "An example from a native executable:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/logging.adoc
msgid "Setting `INFO` as the minimum log level forces checks for lower levels, such as `isTraceEnabled()`, always to return `false`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/logging.adoc
msgid "In turn, code such as `if (logger.isDebugEnabled()) callMethod();` is identified as never executed, also known as dead code."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/logging.adoc
msgid "If you add these properties on the command line, ensure the `\"` character is escaped properly:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/logging.adoc
msgid "All potential properties are listed in the <<loggingConfigurationReference,logging configuration reference>> section."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: _versions/3.34/guides/logging.adoc
msgid "Logging categories"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/logging.adoc
msgid ""
"Logging is configured per category.\n"
"Configuration for a category applies recursively to all subcategories unless a more specific subcategory configuration exists."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/logging.adoc
msgid ""
"The parent of all logging categories is called the \"root category.\"\n"
"As the ultimate parent, this category might contain a configuration that applies globally to all other categories.\n"
"This includes the globally configured handlers and formatters."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: _versions/3.34/guides/logging.adoc
msgid "An example of a global configuration that applies to all categories:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/logging.adoc
msgid "In this example, the root category is configured to use two named handlers: `con` and `mylog`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: _versions/3.34/guides/logging.adoc
msgid "An example of a per-category configuration:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/logging.adoc
msgid "This example shows how to configure the minimal log level for the categories `org.apache.kafka.clients` and `org.apache.kafka.common.utils`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/logging.adoc
msgid "For more information, see <<loggingConfigurationReference>>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/logging.adoc
msgid "If you want to configure something extra for a specific category, create a named handler like `quarkus.log.handler.[console|file|syslog].<your-handler-name>.*` and set it up for that category by using `quarkus.log.category.<my-category>.handlers`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/logging.adoc
msgid "An example use case can be a desire to use a different timestamp format for log messages which are saved to a file than the format used for other handlers."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/3.34/guides/logging.adoc
msgid "For further demonstration, see the outputs of the <<category-named-handlers-example,Attaching named handlers to a category>> example."
msgstr ""

